commentTextItems.html: its on legstump and its easy to clip down to long leg for the winning run. New Zealand win!

commentPostTextItems.html: Even with a few wickets falling at the end, its the second comfortable win in the Tri-series for New Zealand.
It looked at the break that Bangladesh's score was a little below par and that's what it proved.
With all of the New Zealand batsmen getting in, they never had to take any risks. Both Latham and Neesham managed to make it to fifty. Completing the victory with 15 balls to spare.
In a game where we have had five players score over fifty, Jimmy Neesham has just been named man of the match.
With today's win New Zealand stretch their lead at the top of the table, with 8 points. Both Bangladesh and Ireland are stuck on two.
The great news is that both of those teams will have the opportunity to close the gap on the leaders this Friday.
When we are back at Malahide, the game will start at 10:45am. I'll be there and I hope that you can join me too. Until then, this is Justin saying goodnight from Clontarf.

commentTextItems.html: its smashed to the wide long-off boundary and the scores are tied.
pitched up and smashed back past the bowler, hits Umpire Neill on the arm and he doesn't flinch. They still manage to run a couple
another boundary. Santner lifts this ball back down the ground. Mid-off in interested for a second and then it just goes over his head. Less then 10 needed now

commentTextItems.html: tries to cramp Munro for room again, clips the ball off the pads towards the mid-wicket boundary.
that easies some of the pressure, its full and Munro pulls the ball to the mid-wicket boundary.
goes down the legside and Rahim is claiming a catch, must have been the pad because its not out and its not a wide...
gets a large stride in and drives the ball to wide mid-off, 16 needed off 22
good length ball from the bowler, Santner gets onto the front foot and defends the ball into the off-side

commentTextItems.html: tough chance there. It comes off the outside edge and lands just in front of Mustafizur at short third man. The type of ball that if you mis-judge it you can lose some teeth
full ball, Munro hits the ball back down the pitch. Mortaza dives to the ground to stop the ball
looks to cut the ball square on the off-side, goes straight to Mahmudullah at point and so they decide against it
Neesham only half pushes through the ball and it pops up back past the bowler, no fielder at mid-off to take the catch
hits the ball out towards extra cover, sets off for the run. The throw comes into the non-strikers end and hits Munro as he makes his ground
has him tempted into pushing at the ball outside off-stump, doesn't get the edge and it goes through to the keeper

commentPostTextItems.html: 20 runs needed now for a NZ win, Mehedi continues
Or does he, Mortaza has decided to take over instead.

headshotImage.longCaption: Ish Sodhi player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Soumya Sarkar c Latham b Sodhi 61 (67b 5x4 0x6) SR: 91.04

dismissalComment.html: Sarkar gets down to play the sweep and doesn't get over the ball. It flies high in the air and not very far, Latham runs in from short mid-wicket and takes the catch.

headshotImage.caption: Ish Sodhi player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ish Sodhi player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c Neesham b Sodhi 6 (14b 1x4 0x6) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: you could feel the pressure building up with Shakib, not being able to get the ball away. Chips the ball in the air to wide mid-off and Neesham dives forward to take the two handed catch

headshotImage.caption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c †Ronchi b Neesham 55 (66b 4x4 1x6) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: Rahim looks to angle the ball down to third man, gets to fine an edge on it and Ronchi dives to his right to take a good full length catch.

headshotImage.caption: Hamish Bennett player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Hamish Bennett player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah c Rance b Bennett 51 (56b 6x4 0x6) SR: 91.07

dismissalComment.html: What a Catch! Its smashed high in the air and Rance has to run back from short fine leg and take a swirling catch over his shoulder. Great fielding.

dismissalComment.html: looks to flick the ball over the top of Rance at short fine leg, gets no air on it and its an easy catch

headshotImage.caption: Hamish Bennett player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Hamish Bennett player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza run out (†Ronchi) 1 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: pulls the ball to the deep mid-wicket boundary. The throw comes back in like a tracer bullet and after checking with the TV Umpire, Mortaza has to go.

dismissalText.commentary: Tom Latham c †Mushfiqur Rahim b Rubel Hossain 54 (64b 3x4 1x6) SR: 84.37

dismissalComment.html: big wicket for Bangladesh, Latham's gone. Its a good length ball from the bowler, Latham pushes the bat at the ball and gets an inside edge which Rahim gleefully gobbles up and then goes off on a run.

headshotImage.caption: Mustafizur Rahman player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mustafizur Rahman player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Luke Ronchi c Mahmudullah b Mustafizur Rahman 27 (27b 4x4 1x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: its good thinking from the bowler, Ronchi is going for everything and so its another slower ball. It goes high in the air and Mahmudullah gets under the ball at mid-off and takes the catch

headshotImage.caption: Mosaddek Hossain player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mosaddek Hossain player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: George Worker run out (Sabbir Rahman) 17 (24b 0x4 1x6) SR: 70.83

dismissalComment.html: drops the ball into the off-side and Worker is chasing down the other end. He puts in a dive and doesn't beat the throw back in, they check with the TV Umpire and he is out. What a poor decision.

headshotImage.caption: Mustafizur Rahman player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mustafizur Rahman player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor lbw b Mustafizur Rahman 25 (40b 1x4 0x6) SR: 62.5

dismissalComment.html: Taylor is still trying to play the ball into the legside, its full and straight from Mustafizur and hits him on the pads. It's in front of the stumps and its out.
